        <abstract abstract-type="toc" id="Abs3">
          <title>eTOC blurb/In brief</title>
          <p id="P4">By generating paired chemonaive and chemoresistant small cell lung cancer (SCLC) patient derived xenograft models, Gardner et al. find that EZH2 promotes chemoresistance by epigenetically silencing <italic toggle="yes">SLFN11</italic>. EZH2 inhibition prevents acquisition of chemoresistance and improves chemotherapeutic efficacy in SCLC.</p>
        </abstract>
